frameDefinitions: An Agent causes a Dryee (either a surface or an entire entity, inside and out) to become dry.
In this frame an Agent continues to possess a Theme for a Duration of time. '' 'In her heart she must retain bitterness against those who had killed him.'
In this frame, an Agent changes the temperature of an Item.
An Agent causes a Patient to be wet with a Liquid.
In this frame a Source_emitter discharges its Emission along a Path or to a Goal.  ' (1)
frameExamples: In her heart she must <t>retain</t> bitterness against those who had killed him.
Margaret Anne <t>chilled</t> the salad to 30 degrees.
(1) The factory <t>exudes</t> toxic fumes from three large chimneys.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person performing the intentional act causing the <fen>Dryee</fen> to become dry.
The <fen>Dryee</fen> is the entity which has the water removed from it.
An animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that produces the state of dryness. Volitionality is not a necessary characteristic of <fen>Cause</fen>s.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> intentionally affects the <fen>Dryee</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Agent</fen> intentionally affects the <fen>Dryee</fen>.
The person who has possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The entity which the <fen>Agent</fen> possesses for a <fen>Duration</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> has possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> keeps the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> performs the intentional act which changes the temperature of the <fen>Item</fen>.
The <fen>Item</fen> undergoes the temperature change.
An animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that changes the temperature. Volitionality is not a necessary characteristic of <fen>Cause</fen>s.
The <fen>Hot_Cold_source</fen> is the source of the heat or coolness.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when  the <fen>Agent</fen> changes the temperature of the <fen>Item</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where  the <fen>Agent</fen> changes the temperature of the <fen>Item</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is a volitional animate being who causes the <fen>Patient</fen> to become wet.
The <fen>Liquid</fen> is a fluid or gas that permeates or covers the <fen>Patient</fen>.  It most frequently occurs in a PP Complement headed by with.
The <fen>Patient</fen> takes up the <fen>Liquid</fen> through its pores or has the <fen>Liquid</fen> covering its surface.
An animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that produces the state of wetness.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> wets the <fen>Patient</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Agent</fen> wets the <fen>Patient</fen>.
The <fen>Source_emitter</fen> is the item  from which the <fen>Emission</fen> are discharged.
The <fen>Emission</fen>s are discharged out of the <fen>Source_emitter</fen> .
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when  the <fen>Source_emitter</fen> emits the <fen>Emission</fen>.
listRoleExamples: At all times <fex>the Saxon government</fex> held on to its insistently practiced political tradition.
Once you've got a War Bond, hang on to <fex>it</fex> for the full ten years of its life.
Margerite held on to the key <fex>on Wednesday</fex> until I returned to pick it up.
He will retain <fex>in his heart</fex> the memory of the vast Holocaust.
<fex>Ryan</fex> reheated the pasta in the microwave.
Ryan reheated <fex>the pasta</fex> in the microwave.
<fex>Hannah</fex> drenched the cat with anti-flea ointment.
